lessons.theory:
## Functions
Dart supports traditional functions and fat-arrow syntax for single-line functions.
```dart
int add(int a, int b) {
  return a + b;
}
int multiply(int a, int b) => a * b;
```

lessons.starterCode:
int subtract(int a, int b) => ___;

void main() {
  print(subtract(10, 4));
}

lessons.solution:
int subtract(int a, int b) => a - b;
void main() {
  print(subtract(10, 4));
}

lessons.theory:
## Classes & Mixins
Dart is an OOP language. Mixins allow reusing class code in multiple class hierarchies.
```dart
class User { String name; User(this.name); }
mixin Logger { void log(String msg) => print('LOG: $msg'); }
class Admin extends User with Logger { Admin(String n) : super(n); }
```

lessons.starterCode:
mixin Swimmer {
  void swim() => print('Swimming...');
}

class Player with ___ {
  String name;
  Player(this.name);
}

void main() {
  var p = Player('Ada');
  p.___();
}

lessons.solution:
mixin Swimmer {
  void swim() => print('Swimming...');
}
class Player with Swimmer {
  String name;
  Player(this.name);
}
void main() {
  var p = Player('Ada');
  p.swim();
}

lessons.theory:
## Null Safety
Variables cannot be null by default. Use `?` to allow null.
```dart
String? maybeName = null;
String definiteName = maybeName ?? 'Guest';
```

lessons.solution:
String? nickname = null;
void main() {
  print(nickname ?? 'No Nickname');
}

