## HTTP Requests
Use the `http` package to communicate with backends.
```dart
var response = await http.get(Uri.parse('https://api.example.com/data'));
print(response.body);
```

lessons.starterCode:
import 'package:http/http.dart' as http;

Future<String> fetchUsers() ___ {
  var response = await ___.___(___.parse('https://api.mabel.com/users'));
  return response.___;
}

lessons.solution:
import 'package:http/http.dart' as http;
Future<String> fetchUsers() async {
  var response = await http.get(Uri.parse('https://api.mabel.com/users'));
  return response.body;
}

